The Kebbi State Government has given automatic employment to the best graduating medical student of the Usman Danfodiyo University, Sokoto, Asmau Nurudeen Bello, an indigene of the state. The government also gave automatic employment to other 44 medical graduates from Sudan University. Governor Abubakar Atiku Bagudu disclosed this at a dinner organised by his wife, Zainab, in their honour. Bagudu reaffirmed his commitment to providingan enabling environment for indigenes of the state to study anywhere in the world. He expressed delight with the performance of the medical doctors which he said would greatly boost the stateâ€™s health sector. Mrs Bagudu said Asmau would be supported for her residency programme in any institution of her choice.